Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Handle to sharpish turn. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol. Clay fine beige; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Probably drawn by Petrie (EES XVII p.51, 7). Name Ieron. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, BIBALEX 0363.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0536)
